What does the following method return when called with the list [1, 2, 3, 2, 4, 2, 5]?
```java
public static ArrayList<Integer> removeAll(ArrayList<Integer> list, int val) {
    ArrayList<Integer> result = new ArrayList<Integer>();
    for (int item : list) {
        if (item != val) {
            result.add(item);
        }
    }
    return result;
}
// Called as: removeAll(list, 2)
